Description: CroptimizR provides functions for estimating crop models parameters 
   using observations and simulations. It offers a generic framework for linking
   crop models with up-to-date and ad-hoc parameter estimation  algorithms 
   implemented in external packages. It proposes a standard interface for crop 
   models, a set of adapted goodness-of-fit criteria and additional 
   functionalities, including: 1/ Fine tuning of the selected optimization 
   algorithm through specific options; 2/ specification of initial values and 
   constraints on the estimated parameters; 3/ dynamic execution of
   user-defined transformations for observed and/or simulated values in case 
   they would not be directly comparable; 4/ forcing of crop model parameters; 
   and 5/ modulating the level of additional information in output of the 
   parameter estimation process.
